You continue walking and slowly turn around only to see a vehicle that looks oddly familar. As the window rolls down your heart drops as the realization sets in.

The same man that you lied to before rolls down his window and looks at you with a confused face.

"You still out here?" asked the man.

You nervously turn towards the man and stick with the lie you told him before.

"Yeah, my boyfriend's car broke down on the way here." You immediately regret saying that and the man begins to take on a worried look.

"I was just heading back from town, but I wouldn't mind giving you a ride." the man claims. 

You begin to feel bad that you're going to wast ethis man's time, but you really have no other choice.

"Are you sure? I don't want to waste your gas or time."

The man chuckles and reassures you that it's not a problem. He then asks [[where you're headed|Just go with the man]].